init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're given the choice of taking the drug or dying.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you don't, you'll die anyway.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I have been given a second chance at life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I have been given a second chance to make the world a better place.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I have decided to use my time to help the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He tells me that he is here to take me to the government.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You were given a form when you took the drug.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I grabbed my coat and followed the man to the car.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He just started the car and drove away.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were in the middle of nowhere.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The man led me inside and we walked down a long hallway.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He stopped at a door and opened it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You are now the President of the United States."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're the only one who can do this job.
